         Reasoning behind Mags' annoying style:</P><P>I think Mags is adopting a cryptic and obscure style unique to everyone else's style of writing in order to avoid dealing with us on the same level of discussion. It also allows him to feel and be looked upon as different and unique and likely, on a level above that which we supposedly are on. This leads me to think that his style has evolved from past message board experiences in which he was met with the same hostility in reply to his militant stance. His style of being obscure serves to try and offset any sort of crafted, reasoned reply most people are accustomed to as well as make himself feel superior in being able to confuse others with what he thinks are intelligent replies. If he truly believes in what he is writing, I would say he is seriously delusional. If he is writing this all as a joke, it would be damn well crafted. I'm leaning towards delusional. <BR>Seems that the point of his posts are simply to bitch and whine about twitching but as it is such a minor thing in the game (at least it is for me when I play) I don't see the reason behind getting so angry over it. The only reason I can figure out is that this has become a neutral concept that he can use to gain notoriety from. And doing a good job of it as well I might add. No different it seems than what other people do. People like to become and be seen as experts in some highly specialized area of knowledge. But aggravating the people who play the same class in the process for what seems to be the sake of your own notoriety? What the hell?</P><P>If there is some other reason for him to involve himself in such a minor concept other than for the sake of notoriety, enlighten me. I don't see why else a person would go through this kind of trouble for something I do rarely in downtime situations. I don't see any other point to his posts other than veiled trolling. Although they aggravate me, I generally ignore them if I see them simply because this is what I think he intends these posts to be. </P><P>So what to do? Vision(tm) won't ban him and I believe in Free Speech. <BR>Perhaps this approach is best as others will see the full unmoderated history of his posts and our responses. If he does it on other boards, we can post corrections there when we see them (if we care) and/or give reference to past (unmoderated) threads here. We can adapt to the situation given what we have. Isn't that what we do best<BR>and love about our class?</P><P>And now for something completely different... Nuum's latest approach to dealing with Mags reminded me of a fable in which the North Wind challenges the Sun to see who can remove the coat from a man they saw on the earth the fastest. The North Wind tried to blow the coat from the man but the man held on to his coat tighter as the NW blew harder. The NW gave up and the Sun gave it a go. The Sun just shone on the man. Gradually, the Sun shone brighter and brighter to the point where the man simply took off his coat from the warmth.</P><P>Vathex Inthuul'Chath<BR>59 Defiler / Morell-Thule</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
