        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Sure was a long grind to get to the end of this thread.  My take, for what it's worth... Mags is a classic board troll.  Nothing makes him happier than having his opinion anger someone enough to attack him, so he can return fire.  His opinions seem deeply held, and I can respect his commitment to his ideals.  I disagree with him, and that's MY right.  Not that I expect any respect from him.</P><P>Let's see, I expect to hear about my low post number, so lets take care of that first.  I'm running a currently 34th necro on Luclin, but I have multiple characters over 40 on 3 servers and my main is a 56 wizard.  Mostly I lurk here, gathering information, and I simply don't post to speak of.  I've seen a quite a few raids in my time, and know a bit about the high end game &lt;not endgame, but on up there&gt;. If you're on a big raid and you don't do ANYTHING thats needed and within your power to do when its needful, you're a fool.  Do I want to endure a wipeout on a chardok royals raid because the necro would not twitch a cleric?  Hell no!  You use your spells and skills the best you can.  I suspect that clerics don't get a real big charge out of casting CH over and over on the main tank, but thay damn well do it.</P><P>I'm not defending the whole twitchwhore thing.  Any guildleader who had the gall to tell me that all I was good for was to twitch whoever I was told would be told (damn quickly) to go piss up a rope, followed by /guildremove - not that I would join a guild with such a moron running it.   </P><P>I enjoy my necro a lot.  I don't need to fool with finding a group but I can group if I want. I'm still learning my capabilities.  Maybe I wasn't here for the Great Necro Nerf... but if you think that I have not played classes that were gutted, or owned gear that was nerfed or removed from the game, you're wrong.  Basically any class board you cruise will have threads wailing about how something or other was nerfed and oh the unfairness of it all.  S hit happens, get over it.  Sometimes VI even does something right and helps out a bit.  Either way Mags, shuddup and play.  You take this stuff Waaaaay too seriously.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
